title: paintingSuccessExamination
---
<<set $aidanBryant to true>>
<<set $dateCode to true>>
<<set $vibrantVistas to true>>
-> [nomarkup][You squat and squint your eyes trying to read what is written on the piece of paper glued to the canvas.][/nomarkup]
{$kieran}: Vibrant Vistas Gallery... the address... I believe it's somewhere in the Art's District. And the date. 17th June 1969. Probably a date when it was bought.
<<if GetIsPartyMemberRecruited($anastasia) is true and $paintingsAreDestroyed ==true>>
    {$anastasia}: Great! Now we know where we can find more pieces to rip and shred our appreciation for. \[She chuckles.\]
<<endif>>
[nomarkup][Your attention goes to small handwritten note on the stamp - “For my beloved Diana for one of her most important days in her life. Aidan Foster.”][/nomarkup]
-> {$pcName}: Did you heard of any Aidan Foster by any chance?
<<if GetIsPartyMemberRecruited($anastasia) is true>>
    {$anastasia}: \[Anastasia shooks her head.\] Not that I pay any attention to the guys. \[She shrugged.\]
<<endif>>
[nomarkup][Kieran on the other hand looks like he is thinking.][/nomarkup]
<<if GetIsPartyMemberRecruited($anastasia) is true>>
    {$anastasia}: Our nerd guy seems to have an idea though.
    {$kieran}: You're right ms Goth Queen. I have.
<<endif>>
{$kieran}: I believe that Aidan Foster was Diana's husband. Rather touchy topic for her. He died in 'nam in 1972 from what I recall. Killed in action. Once I accidentally asked her about it. When I was Kate's ghoul I was helping Diana from time to time with the papers and stumbled upon a mail with the guys name.
-> {$pcName}: Good to know. May be important. Thanks Kieran.
<<if $paintingsAreDestroyed ==false>>
    [nomarkup][You leave the painting alone. You will not gain more information from it.][/nomarkup]
<<endif>>
===
